hello ddccontrol users,

i've tried ddccontrol with the 20061014 database as packaged in debian
as 20061014-4, and got the red blinking warning about an unknown
monitor.

the requested output of `LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddccontrol -p -c -d` is attached;
the monitor, a NEC MultiSync LCD2470WVX, is connected on VGA of an intel
965gm chip.

i've made some observations by going through menu items and comparing
the ddccontrol outputs:

0xe3: osd lock out -- 1 =3D locked, 0 =3D unlocked
0xf9: dv mode -- 1 =3D standard, 2 =3D text, 3 =3D movie, 4 =3D gaming,
        5 =3D photo
0x87 =3D 0x8c: sharpness
0x14: rgb mode -- 4 =3D "5 (defaults to 5000K)", 1 =3D "sRGB (6500K)",
	2 =3D "native", 8 =3D "1 (defaults to 9300K)", 7 =3D "2 (defaults to
	8200K)", 6 =3D "3 (defaults to 7500K)"; the numbered settings can
	have their rgb parts customized
0x68 =3D 0xf5: osd language -- 1 =3D english, 2 =3D german, 3 =3D french,
	4 =3D spanish, 5 =3D chinese, 6 =3D italian, 7 =3D swedish, 9 =3D russian,
	8 is not recognized
0xfc: osd shutdown time -- linear, 1 =3D 10", 23 =3D 120"

i've seen the 0xfa and 0xff increase without reason; both have a maximum
value of 65535

some monitor settings seem to be inaccessable from ddccontrol: expansion
mode (aspect / full off), off timer, power led brightness, hot key, osd
position and resolution notifier.

the settings for brightness (0x10), contrast (0x12), positioning (0x20,
0x30, 0x32, 0x0e) and rgb (0x16, 0x18, 0x1a) just worked out of the box.


hoping this report is useful to you
chrysn

